## Accessibility
- Text contrast ≥ 4.5:1 (use Tailwind's color palette which meets WCAG standards)
- Fully tabbable + visible focus states (use `focus:ring-2 focus:ring-teal-500 focus:outline-none`)
- Alt text required for images
- Form errors displayed inline + summary
- Keyboard: all interactive elements focusable (use `focus:ring-*` utilities)

---

## Interaction & Motion
- Transitions: Use Tailwind's `transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out`
- Hover: Use `hover:underline hover:underline-offset-4` for links, `hover:shadow-lg` for cards
- Hover on links: Use `hover:text-teal-500` for color shift
- Card hover: Use `hover:-translate-y-1 hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300`
- Smooth scroll behavior: Use `scroll-smooth` class on `<html>` element
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`: Use `motion-safe:` prefix for animations

---

## Code Conventions
- Semantic HTML (`<header>`, `<main>`, `<nav>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<aside>`, `<footer>`)
- Use Tailwind utility classes first (`flex`, `mb-4`, `text-center`, etc.)
- CSS class naming: Use Tailwind utility classes; follow BEM methodology only for custom component classes when necessary
- Extract **reusable components** as partials/fragments if using a templating system later
- Common sections: Hero, Who We Are, Statistics, Services, Tech Capabilities, Awards, Industries, Recent Work, Process, Comparison Table, Testimonials, Pricing, Blog, FAQs, CTA Banner, Footer

---

## File Structure
- **Assets**: `/assets/css/`, `/assets/js/`, `/assets/images/`
- **CSS**: Main Tailwind input file at `/assets/css/input.css` (with `@tailwind` directives)
- **CSS Output**: Compiled Tailwind CSS at `/assets/css/output.css` (generated from `input.css`)
- **Config**: Tailwind configuration at `/tailwind.config.js` (for custom colors, fonts, spacing, etc.)
- **Custom CSS**: Additional custom styles at `/assets/css/custom.css` (if needed, use sparingly)
- **Components**: Organize reusable HTML components
- **Pages**: Keep main pages in root, sub-pages in `/pages/` if needed

