## Coding Standards

### CSS
- **Use Tailwind CSS utility classes first**, then extend via `tailwind.config.js` or `input.css` if needed
- Configure custom colors, fonts, and spacing in `tailwind.config.js` using the `theme` object
- Avoid using !important - use proper Tailwind utilities or increase specificity
- Use Tailwind's spacing utilities (`m-*`, `p-*`) instead of custom spacing when possible
- Follow Tailwind's utility-first approach; use component classes only when necessary
- Use Tailwind's flexbox and grid utilities for layouts (`flex`, `grid`, `grid-cols-*`)
- Organize custom CSS with comments for sections (Custom Components, Utilities) if using `custom.css`
- Use Tailwind's responsive breakpoints in custom CSS: `@media (min-width: 640px)`, `@media (min-width: 768px)`, etc.

### HTML
- Use semantic HTML elements (`<header>`, `<main>`, `<nav>`, `<section>`, `<footer>`)
- Include Tailwind CSS in `<head>`: 
  - CDN: `<script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>` (for development)
  - Or compiled: `<link href="/assets/css/output.css" rel="stylesheet">` (for production)
- Use Tailwind utility classes for all styling
- Maintain accessibility with proper ARIA labels and semantic HTML
- Keep markup clean and minimal
- No inline styles unless unavoidable (and documented)

### JavaScript
- Use modern ES6+ syntax
- Prefer const and let over var
- Use arrow functions where appropriate
- Handle errors gracefully
- Use the same HTML structure for both desktop and mobile
- Toggle visibility/behavior via JavaScript with Tailwind classes (`hidden`, `block`, `flex`, etc.)

### Icons
- Use inline SVG icons instead of external icon libraries
- Keep SVG code clean and optimized
- Use consistent icon sizing and styling with Tailwind utilities (`w-5 h-5`, `w-6 h-6`, etc.)

### Performance
- Optimize images and assets
- Minimize HTTP requests
- Use Tailwind's purging/content configuration to remove unused CSS in production
- Lazy load non-critical resources
- Mobile-first approach with progressive enhancement

### Tailwind Configuration
- Configure custom colors in `tailwind.config.js`:
```javascript
theme: {
  extend: {
    colors: {
      primary: '#14B8A6',
      secondary: '#1E293B',
    }
  }
}
```
- Configure custom fonts in `tailwind.config.js`:
```javascript
theme: {
  extend: {
    fontFamily: {
      sans: ['Poppins', 'system-ui', 'sans-serif'],
    }
  }
}
```
- Use `content` array in `tailwind.config.js` to specify which files to scan for classes
